markers.description: The Tin City beach huts are one of the very few breaks in the endless monotony of 27 kilometres of beach, but also not.
markers.title: Are We There Yet?

markers.description: A historic military bridge, out here as a surprise outdoor museum piece.
markers.title: It Belongs in a Museum

markers.description: This is legitimately the middle of nowhere, with only solitude surrounding you. May it comfort you during the long long climb ahead.
markers.title: You've Come a Long Way Baby

markers.description: Even after many kilometres of coast, this place still manages to astonish.
markers.title: Tadaa!

markers.description: It's rarely more than a trickle, but it's here exclusively for ones as adventurous as you.
markers.title: Ah! Nice Falls

markers.description: Every point is the top, depending on how you rotate it.
markers.title: The Top of the World

markers.description: Not many come here, but Taffy did.
markers.title: Taffy Was Here

markers.description: You'll be around the hairpin bend downhill, before you realise this hidden view is worth turnning back for.
markers.title: Blink and You'll Miss It

markers.description: Neither campers nor eastern greys can resist these grassy fields.
markers.title: I was Promised Kangaroos

markers.description: If you stand around long enough, there will probably be a train across the valley.
markers.title: So where is it?

markers.description: The start of the Fernleigh railway line, but also the start of an historic trek.
markers.title: I'm a Choo Choo Train: Belmont

markers.description: End of the wetlands and start of suburbia.
markers.title: I'm a Choo Choo Train: Jewells

markers.description: Alight here for Awabakal Nature Reserve and Redhead Beach.
markers.title: I'm a Choo Choo Train: Redhead

markers.description: No longer a stop for trains, but now one for coffee and cakes up there.
markers.title: I'm a Choo Choo Train: Whitebridge

markers.description: Glenrock's a good reason to leave the train here.
markers.title: I'm a Choo Choo Train: Kahibah

markers.description: The narrow tunnel of dense vegetation opens up to expansive coastal heath.
markers.title: The Rear Entrance

markers.description: End of the line for the Fernleigh Track. From here you get to ride a real train.
markers.title: I'm a Choo Choo Train: Adamstown

markers.description: You may be here on the lucky few days there is a historic tram ride to the Sydney Tramway Museum outside the park.
markers.title: Ding Ding Ding!

markers.description: The light is a warning not to sail a ship into the steep cliffs of the coast. Let it also be a reminder not to fall off the same.
markers.title: The Guiding Light

markers.description: The fourth statue of famous explorers requires some exploration to find.
markers.title: Somewhere Out There
